WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.980
We need stronger encryption. Anything less creates too much exposure.

00:00:05.340 --> 00:00:09.740
If we push it that far, performance drops too hard. Real-time use will suffer.

00:00:10.100 --> 00:00:16.060
Two valid priorities. One deadlock. But we can't treat it like one of them has to lose.

00:00:17.640 --> 00:00:21.240
Both of you have valid points, but we can't just focus on one.

00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:26.560
But we can figure out a hybrid approach to this, something that protects the highest risk data,

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:28.740
Something that also keeps the lag down.

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:32.800
The disagreement was useful once the team designed for both truths.
